Citation.sTitle: Excess Molar Enthalpies for Binary Mixtures of Ethanol + Acetone, + Octane, + Cyclohexane and 1-Propanol + Acetone, + Octane, + Heptane at 323.15
Citation.sAbstract: A flow-type isothermal microcalorimeter was used to measure excess enthalpies, HE, of the binary mixtures of ethanol + acetone, + octane, + cyclohexane and 1-propanol + acetone, + octane, + heptane at 323.15 K at atmospheric pressure. The experimental results show that the excess enthalpies of these systems are all endothermic over the entire composition range and their maximum values of HE are in a range of 946.9 J!Emol-1 to 1549.4 J!Emol-1. The data were correlated with a modified Redlich-Kister equation to within experimental uncertainty, except for 1-propanol + acetone.
